Medical Maths

Hi and welcome to ‘Medical Maths’!

About

My name is Becky and I’m a recent maths graduate interested in applications of data science to healthcare. On this site I plan to post articles that use R code and simulations to help explain some interesting computational and statistical concepts, with a focus on medical applications. Hopefully none of the posts should require too much background knowledge of either mathematics or coding in R, and they will all have a linked R Markdown file that you can download and play around with. Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy!

(If you spot an error in any of these articles or have any other feedback or points you want to discuss please feel free to contact me at: medicalmaths@protonmail.com)
